Eighteen public hospitals across SA will receive the newly acquired Johnson & Johnson vaccines on Wednesday. The vaccines arrived in the country on Tuesday night and are the first batch of 80,000 doses of the vaccine which are being distributed across SA. Health ministry spokesperson Popo Maja confirmed the following list of hospitals to TimesLIVE: Staff at the Inkosi Albert Luthuli Central Hospital are awaiting the arrival of the vaccine from the Durban's King Shaka International Airport. The vaccines are expected to arrive via a convoy of police and department of health vehicles. TimesLIVE